body:
this is the same issue you filed previously, right? https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/1601 

it's still on the backlog, so if this is blocking some of your projects, is this something you could contribute?

The only thing I can contribute is make libFuzzer local since this lib has only on Readme.txt inside... no codes..

Also it's not a third lib of onnxruntime, it's a third lib of grpc, and not a third lib of grpc directly, it's a third lib of bloaty which is third lib of grpc which is third lib of onnxruntime.

So .........

I think should make this annoying lib `cmake/external/grpc/third_party/bloaty`  gone....
So, how to just skip this third party sync step?

挂代理多更新几次子模块
git submodule update --init --recursive

after sync libFuzzer error, use following flag to continue build, which can skip git submodule update: 
--skip_submodule_sync

issue.title: [skia] build failure

repository.name: vcpkg
repository.description: C++ Library Manager for Windows, Linux, and MacOS

- Compiler: Visual Studio 2019
